The paper focuses on fingertip detection in human computer interaction, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The proposed method uses binocular images, which involves stereo vision and depth estimation, and the use of convolutional neural networks, which are topics related to robotics (cs.RO), multimedia (cs.MM), and machine learning (cs.LG).
